[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    125[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Services** | Amazon Comprehend, Amazon Comprehend Medical, Amazon S3, AWS Lambda, Amazon DynamoDB, Amazon SQS, Amazon API Gateway |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    126[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **IAM Permissions** | `comprehend:ClassifyDocument`, `comprehend:DetectEntities` (medical), `s3:GetObject`, `s3:PutObject`, `dynamodb:GetItem`, `dynamodb:PutItem`, `sqs:SendMessage` |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    127[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **BAA** | AWS BAA signed (chief complaints are PHI; they describe why a patient is seeking care) |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    128[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Encryption** | S3: SSE-KMS; DynamoDB: encryption at rest (default); SQS: SSE-KMS; all API calls over TLS |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    129[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **VPC** | Production: Lambda in VPC with VPC endpoints for Comprehend, S3, DynamoDB, SQS, and CloudWatch Logs |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    130[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **CloudTrail** | Enabled: log all Comprehend and DynamoDB API calls for HIPAA audit trail |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    131[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Training Data** | Minimum 1,000 labeled examples per category (ideally 5,000+). Historical chief complaints with routing decisions from your institution's EHR. De-identify before use in development. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    132[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Cost Estimate** | Comprehend Custom Classification: $0.0005 per request (real-time endpoint). Comprehend Medical: $0.01 per 100 characters. Lambda and DynamoDB negligible at this scale. Endpoint hosting: ~$0.50/hour per inference unit. |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    133[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    134[0m:[38;5;10m[49m ### Ingredients
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    135[0m:[38;5;10m[49m 
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    136[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | AWS Service | Role |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    137[0m:[38;5;10m[49m |------------|------|
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    138[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Comprehend (Custom)** | Trained multi-class text classifier for chief complaint categories |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    139[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon Comprehend Medical** | Entity detection for preprocessing enrichment and abbreviation disambiguation |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    140[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon S3** | Stores training data and model artifacts |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    141[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **AWS Lambda** | Orchestrates preprocessing, classification, and routing logic |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    142[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon DynamoDB** | Abbreviation expansion table and classification result storage |
[0m[49m[38;5;10m+    143[0m:[38;5;10m[49m | **Amazon SQS** | Dead letter queue for low-confidence classifications needing human review |
